        "created_at": "2025-02-19T18:55:11.975Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I read the article on Signal new chat synchronisation mechanism <a href=\"https://signal.org/blog/a-synchronized-start-for-linked-devices/\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Signal &gt;&gt; Blog &gt;&gt; A Synchronized Start for Linked Devices</a></p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Does the synchronisation take place without the server? Or is it e2ee and the data goes through the server?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Is the function based on SVR 2-3 technology like for contacts and graph? <a href=\"https://github.com/signalapp/SecureValueRecovery2\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">GitHub - signalapp/SecureValueRecovery2</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Why does Signal have a 45 day limit which is not present in other e2ee services?</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Thank you</p>",
