        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/{size}/43780_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-02-19T18:58:14.056Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"alfred\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"67035\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/13edae/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> alfred:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Why does Signal have a 45 day limit which is not present in other e2ee services?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>The 45 day limit is only related to media. This is because media can be rather large and so they don’t transmit the media between devices in order to save time on slow connections; instead, they have the new device download it from the server. However, media only lives on the server for 45 days, so nothing older than that can be retrieved.</p>",
