        "id": 261677,
        "name": "",
        "username": "CueHD",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/cuehd/{size}/42510_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-02-20T14:17:15.199Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"alfred\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"67035\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/13edae/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> alfred:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Does the synchronisation take place without the server? Or is it e2ee and the data goes through the server?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>The chat synchronization mechanism makes a “backup” of all Signal text messages present on the client device initiating the synchronization and of the meta data required to re-download media attachments that are still present (past 45 days) on the server. This backup gets sent to the new client via the server as a special attachment that is end-to-end encrypted. The new client restores this backup, which immediately restores the text messages then re-downloads the media attachments using the meta data from the backup.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"alfred\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"67035\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/13edae/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> alfred:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Is the function based on SVR 2-3 technology like for contacts and graph? <a href=\"https://github.com/signalapp/SecureValueRecovery2\">GitHub - signalapp/SecureValueRecovery2</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>No</p>",
